https://access.redhat.com/support/cases/#/case/new
Summary: ipa-replica-install fails with wait_for_entry timeout on cn=KDC — cannot complete RHEL 8 to RHEL 9 IPA migration before critical deadline
Environment:

Source: cpeg-ipareplica.ipa.calix.local — RHEL 8, IPA 4.9.13, sole CA master
Target: pln-ipamaster.ipa.calix.local — RHEL 9.3, IPA 4.12.2
Hard deadline: March 28 Petaluma DC shutdown — cpeg goes offline

What happened:

ipa-replica-install --setup-ca got through all CA steps successfully (steps 1-33 complete including CA startup)
Failed at final step: wait_for_entry timeout on ldap://cpeg-ipareplica.ipa.calix.local:389 for cn=KDC,cn=pln-ipamaster.ipa.calix.local,cn=masters,cn=ipa,cn=etc,dc=ipa,dc=calix,dc=local
The cn=KDC entry exists on pln but never replicates to cpeg
Root cause: pln → cpeg replication agreement shows Error (18) Can't acquire replica (Incremental update) due to pre-existing CSN purge issue on the changelog
cpeg → pln replication works fine (Error 0)

Current state:

pln has DS, CA (pki-tomcatd), KDC, httpd all running
sysrestore.state shows complete = False
Cannot uninstall pln — CA database took 5+ hours to replicate
Cannot re-initialize cpeg from pln — cpeg is the only working IPA master

What we need:

How to manually complete the replica install or mark it complete after manually injecting the missing cn=masters entries into cpeg
Or how to fix the Error (18) incremental replication from pln to cpeg so the KDC entry pushes over



# Full replication status
ldapsearch -Y EXTERNAL -H ldapi://%2Frun%2Fslapd-IPA-CALIX-LOCAL.socket \
  -b "cn=meTocpeg-ipareplica.ipa.calix.local,cn=replica,cn=dc\3Dipa\2Cdc\3Dcalix\2Cdc\3Dlocal,cn=mapping tree,cn=config" \
  -s base "(objectclass=*)" 2>/dev/null > /tmp/pln-repl-agreement.txt

# Last 500 lines of install log
tail -500 /var/log/ipareplica-install.log > /tmp/pln-install-log.txt

# DS errors log
tail -1000 /var/log/dirsrv/slapd-IPA-CALIX-LOCAL/errors > /tmp/pln-ds-errors.txt

# sysrestore state
cp /var/lib/ipa/sysrestore/sysrestore.state /tmp/pln-sysrestore.txt

# IPA version
ipa --version > /tmp/pln-ipa-version.txt
